---
import { site } from '../../../data/site';
import Wrapper from '../../../layouts/Wrapper.astro';
const contact = `The best way to get in touch with me is via Twitter DM or`;
const jobs = `I'm currently interested in finding a summer internship, with the potential for growth. If you think I may be a fit, id love to work with you.`;
const socailLinks = [site.github, site.linkedIn, site.github];
---

<Wrapper>
  <div class="py-5 my-5">
    <h1 class="font-bold text-7xl my-5">About Me.</h1>
    <h2 class="text-xl max-w-3xl">
      I'm a student at the University of West Florida. I'm studying Computer
      Science with a concentration in A.I and Software Engineering.
    </h2>
    <div class="flex flex-row justify-start py-10">
      <!-- left column -->
      <div class="w-1/3 pr-10">
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-2xl text-gray-50">Contact</h4>'
          <span class="text-md text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-300"
            >{contact}
          </span>
          <a href="mailto:dhuson@davidhuson.dev" class="text-amber-200"
            >email me.
          </a>
        </div>
        <div class="py-3">
          <h4 class="text-2xl">Job Opportunities</h4>
          <span class="text-md">{jobs}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="py-3">
          <h4 class="text-2xl">Social Links</h4>
          <div class="flex flex-col p-1">
            {socailLinks.map((item) => (
              <a
                href={item.link}
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-lg p-2 text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 font-normal"
              >
                â†’ {item.name}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- right column -->
      <div class="w-2/3 pr-10 flex-col">
        <p class="text-lg">
          I've been developing full-stack application since I was 10 years old.
          I didn't know what full-stack meant at that time because the term was
          not coined back then. I'm so out of content right now that I'm
          literally crying writing this text since lorem text is so 2012 now.
        </p>
        <p class="pt-2">
          After learning HTML and struggling with CSS, I came up with a
          brilliant idea of using bootstrap so that I don't have to style
          everything by myself and - for obvious reasons - if you knew
          bootstrap, you were cool. But now, I'm a legend. I've been coding in
          React, Angular, Vue, Svelte, Node.js, Express, Fastify, MongoDB,
          MySQL, Bootstrap, Tailwind, C, C++, C#, Rust, Haskell, Perl, PHP,
          Assembly, Logo and YouDontKnowShit programming language etc to name a
          few. Although I barely know the syntax (Psst, Stack overflow!), I
          consider myself a Ninja developer I'm laughing right now.
        </p>
        <div>
          <h4 class="text-4xl py-5">Technologies I'm Comfortable with</h4>
          <div class="flex">
            <i class="devicon-cplusplus-plain text-7xl text-slate-200 mr-3"></i>
            <i class="devicon-java-plain-wordmark text-7xl text-slate-200 mr-3"
            ></i>
            <i class="devicon-javascript-plain colored text-7xl mr-3"></i>
            <i class="devicon-typescript-plain colored text-7xl mr-3"></i>
            <i class="devicon-react-original colored text-7xl mr-3"></i>
            <i class="devicon-graphql-plain colored text-7xl mr-3"></i>
            <i class="devicon-mysql-plain colored text-7xl mr-3"></i>
            <i class="devicon-nodejs-plain colored text-7xl mr-3"></i>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Wrapper>
